511
00:40:24,754 --> 00:40:26,522
No, I've already had my cup.

512
00:40:26,589 --> 00:40:28,124
Is there sugar?

513
00:40:29,459 --> 00:40:30,776
Sugar?

514
00:40:32,228 --> 00:40:38,767
Yes, yes. Somewhere here.

515
00:40:40,437 --> 00:40:43,071
I put it in the drawer
for Lent last year.

516
00:40:43,139 --> 00:40:44,740
Never remembered
to take it out.

517
00:40:44,808 --> 00:40:46,809
It mustn't have been
much to give up, then.

518
00:40:49,679 --> 00:40:52,381
I'm sure you're right.
Here it is.

519
00:40:52,449 --> 00:40:59,088
I'll serve you, although for want
of practice I'm a little clumsy.

520
00:41:00,957 --> 00:41:02,758
I see your fingernails.

521
00:41:04,711 --> 00:41:06,628
Wear them a little long.

522
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:09,214
The sugar?
Yes. One?

523
00:41:09,282 --> 00:41:10,482
Three.

524
00:41:11,484 --> 00:41:13,418
Three?
Sweet tooth.

525
00:41:13,919 --> 00:41:16,856
Two. Three.

526
00:41:18,024 --> 00:41:19,558
Sister, you care for sugar?

527
00:41:19,625 --> 00:41:21,193
Never.

528
00:41:21,261 --> 00:41:24,246
Not that there's anything
wrong with sugar.

529
00:41:25,648 --> 00:41:28,517
Well, thank you, Father,
for making time for us.

530
00:41:28,585 --> 00:41:30,285
We are at our wit's end.

531
00:41:30,353 --> 00:41:34,572
I think it's an excellent idea to
rethink the Christmas pageant,

532
00:41:34,640 --> 00:41:37,743
'cause last year's effort
was a little woebegone.

533
00:41:37,811 --> 00:41:41,714
Oh, I loved it, but I love all pageants.
The hymns.

534
00:41:41,781 --> 00:41:45,200
<i>O Little Town of Bethlehem, O Come,
O Come, Emmanuel, O Come...</i>

535
00:41:45,268 --> 00:41:47,603
All right.
Thank you, Sister James.

536
00:41:47,670 --> 00:41:49,037
So what do you think, Father?

537
00:41:49,105 --> 00:41:51,239
Is there
something new we could do?

538
00:41:51,307 --> 00:41:53,809
Well, we all love
the Christmas hymns,

539
00:41:53,877 --> 00:41:58,047
but it might be jolly
to include a secular song.

540
00:41:58,115 --> 00:42:00,015
Secular?
Yes.

541
00:42:00,033 --> 00:42:03,168
<i>It's Beginning To Look A Lot Like
Christmas.</i> Something like that.

542
00:42:03,236 --> 00:42:06,839
What would be the point
of a secular song?

543
00:42:06,907 --> 00:42:08,140
Just fun.

544
00:42:08,207 --> 00:42:09,274
Or <i>Frosty the Snowman.</i>

545
00:42:09,342 --> 00:42:10,893
That's a good one.

546
00:42:10,960 --> 00:42:14,847
We could have one of the boys dress
up as a snowman, dance around.

547
00:42:15,498 --> 00:42:16,866
Which boy?

548
00:42:20,887 --> 00:42:22,454
We'd do tryouts.

549
00:42:22,522 --> 00:42:27,125
<i>Frosty the Snowman espouses
a pagan belief in magic.</i>

550
00:42:27,194 --> 00:42:31,197
The snowman comes to life when an
enchanted hat is put on his head.

551
00:42:31,264 --> 00:42:32,964
If the music were more somber,

552
00:42:33,032 --> 00:42:38,020
people would realize the images are
disturbing and the song heretical.

553
00:42:38,087 --> 00:42:41,490
I never thought about <i>Frosty
the Snowman</i> like that.

554
00:42:41,558 --> 00:42:42,758
It should be banned
from the airwaves.

555
00:42:42,825 --> 00:42:45,077
So, not <i>Frosty the Snowman.</i>

556
00:42:45,144 --> 00:42:51,116
Oh, <i>It's Beginning To Look A Lot Like
Christmas</i> would be fine, I suppose.

557
00:42:51,184 --> 00:42:53,118
Parents would like it.

558
00:42:55,105 --> 00:42:59,391
May I ask what you're writing
down with that ballpoint pen?

559
00:42:59,459 --> 00:43:03,362
Oh, nothing.
It's an idea for a sermon.

560
00:43:03,430 --> 00:43:04,863
Oh. You had one
right now?

561
00:43:04,931 --> 00:43:07,249
I get them all the time.

562
00:43:07,317 --> 00:43:09,084
How fortunate.

563
00:43:09,086 --> 00:43:11,453
I forget them, so I have
to write them down.

564
00:43:11,521 --> 00:43:12,838
Oh.

565
00:43:12,906 --> 00:43:14,689
What is the idea?

566
00:43:16,726 --> 00:43:18,194
Intolerance.

567
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:25,534
Would you like
a little more tea, Father?

568
00:43:25,601 --> 00:43:26,935
Not yet.

569
00:43:28,655 --> 00:43:30,973
It's a new time, Sister.

570
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:32,040
What's new about it?

571
00:43:32,108 --> 00:43:34,093
Something inside
of people is new.

572
00:43:34,160 --> 00:43:36,828
There is nothing new
under the sun.

573
00:43:39,866 --> 00:43:43,001
The Church needs to change.

574
00:43:43,068 --> 00:43:45,937
We should sing a song
from the radio now and then,

575
00:43:46,005 --> 00:43:47,740
take the kids out
for ice cream.

576
00:43:47,807 --> 00:43:49,107
Sweet tooth.

577
00:43:49,175 --> 00:43:52,094
And maybe take the boys
on a camping trip.

578
00:43:52,162 --> 00:43:53,846
The point being?

579
00:43:55,048 --> 00:43:57,733
We should be friendlier.

580
00:43:57,800 --> 00:43:59,768
You know, the children
and the parents

581
00:43:59,836 --> 00:44:02,337
should see us
as members of their family.

582
00:44:02,405 --> 00:44:07,526
But we are not members of their family.
We're different.

583
00:44:07,593 --> 00:44:10,195
Why?
Because of our vows?

584
00:44:11,114 --> 00:44:13,481
Precisely.

585
00:44:13,549 --> 00:44:15,767
I don't think
we're so different.

586
00:44:15,835 --> 00:44:17,735
You know, Sister,
I would take some more tea.

587
00:44:17,803 --> 00:44:20,773
And they think
we're different, yeah?

588
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:22,474
The working...

589
00:44:22,542 --> 00:44:28,079
The working class people of this
parish trust us to be different.

590
00:44:28,147 --> 00:44:29,648
I think we're getting
off the subject.

591
00:44:29,716 --> 00:44:31,316
Yes, you're right. You're right.
You're right. Back to it.

592
00:44:38,692 --> 00:44:40,058
Yes?

593
00:44:40,126 --> 00:44:43,862
Sister Raymond? Mmm.

594
00:44:43,930 --> 00:44:48,049
Well, you tell her to wash her face and
her neck and report to me at 3:00.

595
00:44:48,118 --> 00:44:49,501
Yeah.

596
00:44:51,103 --> 00:44:54,540
Excuse me.
The Christmas pageant.

597
00:44:55,608 --> 00:44:57,676
We must be careful

598
00:44:57,744 --> 00:44:59,494
how Donald Miller is used
in the pageant.

599
00:44:59,562 --> 00:45:01,045
Easy there, Sister.

600
00:45:01,113 --> 00:45:02,547
Father.

601
00:45:08,271 --> 00:45:10,172
All right, what about
Donald Miller?

602
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:12,357
We must be careful,
in the pageant,

603
00:45:12,425 --> 00:45:16,562
that we neither hide Donald
Miller nor put him forward.

604
00:45:19,899 --> 00:45:21,499
Because of the color
of his skin?

605
00:45:21,567 --> 00:45:23,318
That's right, yeah.

606
00:45:23,385 --> 00:45:24,903
Why?

607
00:45:25,771 --> 00:45:27,139
Oh, come, Father.

608
00:45:27,206 --> 00:45:31,309
I think he should be treated
like every other boy.

609
00:45:31,377 --> 00:45:35,647
Well, you yourself singled the
boy out for special attention.

610
00:45:38,084 --> 00:45:43,538
You held a private meeting with
him at the rectory. A week ago?

611
00:45:43,606 --> 00:45:44,974
Yes.

612
00:45:48,611 --> 00:45:50,862
What are we talking about?

613
00:45:51,431 --> 00:45:52,881
Donald Miller.

614
00:45:56,486 --> 00:45:59,821
The boy acted strangely
when he returned to class.

615
00:46:01,457 --> 00:46:02,941
He did?

616
00:46:03,009 --> 00:46:06,478
When he returned from the
rectory, a little odd, yes.

617
00:46:07,013 --> 00:46:08,813
Can you tell us why?

618
00:46:11,067 --> 00:46:13,017
How did he act strangely?

619
00:46:13,836 --> 00:46:14,869
He...

620
00:46:16,105 --> 00:46:18,973
I'm not sure how to explain it.

621
00:46:19,041 --> 00:46:21,476
He laid his head
on the desk and...

622
00:46:25,215 --> 00:46:26,615
Do you mean
you had some impression?

623
00:46:26,682 --> 00:46:28,116
Yes.

624
00:46:28,184 --> 00:46:30,418
And he'd come from the
rectory, so you're asking me?

625
00:46:30,486 --> 00:46:31,804
Mmm. That's it.

626
00:46:32,538 --> 00:46:33,906
Hmm.

627
00:46:33,973 --> 00:46:35,140
Mmm.

628
00:46:35,842 --> 00:46:36,741
Mmm.

629
00:46:38,411 --> 00:46:40,378
Did you want to discuss the pageant?
Is that why I'm here?

630
00:46:40,446 --> 00:46:42,431
Or is this what
you wanted to discuss?

631
00:46:43,148 --> 00:46:44,266
This.

632
00:46:45,918 --> 00:46:48,836
Well, I'm a little
uncomfortable.

633
00:46:48,904 --> 00:46:50,021
Why?

634
00:46:50,089 --> 00:46:51,890
Why do you think?

635
00:46:51,957 --> 00:46:54,159
The boy's well-being
is my responsibility.

636
00:46:56,161 --> 00:46:57,579
His well-being
is not at issue.

637
00:46:57,647 --> 00:47:01,065
I'm not satisfied
that that is true.

638
00:47:01,133 --> 00:47:04,887
He was upset
when he returned to class.

639
00:47:04,954 --> 00:47:06,521
Did he say something?

640
00:47:06,589 --> 00:47:07,556
No.

641
00:47:09,242 --> 00:47:10,859
What happened in the rectory?

642
00:47:12,345 --> 00:47:13,495
Happened?

643
00:47:13,513 --> 00:47:14,880
Mmm.

644
00:47:14,948 --> 00:47:16,364
Nothing happened.
I had a talk with the boy.

645
00:47:16,432 --> 00:47:17,699
What about?

646
00:47:17,766 --> 00:47:18,934
Private matter.

647
00:47:19,001 --> 00:47:22,187
He's 12 years old.
What could be private?

648
00:47:24,507 --> 00:47:26,341
- Should I get...
- No.

649
00:47:27,777 --> 00:47:30,279
I object to your tone.

650
00:47:30,346 --> 00:47:36,417
This is not about my tone
or your tone, Father Flynn.

651
00:47:39,021 --> 00:47:40,989
It's about
arriving at the truth.

652
00:47:41,056 --> 00:47:42,557
Of what?

653
00:47:42,625 --> 00:47:48,230
You know what I'm talking
about, don't you?

654
00:47:48,232 --> 00:47:53,017
And you're controlling the expression
on your face right now, aren't you?

655
00:47:53,085 --> 00:47:54,485
My face?

656
00:47:57,023 --> 00:47:58,556
What exactly
are you accusing me of?

657
00:47:58,624 --> 00:48:01,325
I'm not accusing you
of anything, Father Flynn.

658
00:48:01,393 --> 00:48:07,031
I am asking you to tell me
what happened in the rectory.

659
00:48:13,522 --> 00:48:16,875
I don't wish to continue this.

660
00:48:16,942 --> 00:48:18,393
And if you're
dissatisfied with that,

661
00:48:18,461 --> 00:48:22,497
I suggest you speak
to Monsignor Benedict.

662
00:48:22,564 --> 00:48:26,918
I can only imagine this unfortunate
behavior is the result of overwork.

663
00:48:28,187 --> 00:48:31,055
Have a good morning,
Sister. Sister.

664
00:48:36,179 --> 00:48:40,599
There was alcohol on his breath

665
00:48:42,551 --> 00:48:45,520
when he returned
from his meeting with you.

666
00:48:49,508 --> 00:48:50,758
Alcohol?

667
00:48:52,678 --> 00:48:54,946
I did smell it on his breath.

668
00:49:00,519 --> 00:49:01,753
Well?

669
00:49:05,942 --> 00:49:07,692
Let this alone.
No.

670
00:49:17,470 --> 00:49:20,973
Take your time, Father.
Would you like some more tea?

671
00:49:22,374 --> 00:49:24,526
You should've let it alone.

672
00:49:26,446 --> 00:49:27,946
Not possible.

673
00:49:36,138 --> 00:49:39,274
Mr. McGuinn caught Donald
drinking altar wine.

674
00:49:41,110 --> 00:49:47,849
When I found out, I sent for him.
There were tears,

675
00:49:47,917 --> 00:49:53,888
and he begged not to be removed from
the altar boys. I took pity on him.

676
00:49:53,956 --> 00:49:57,242
I told him if no one else found
out, I'd let him stay on.

677
00:49:57,310 --> 00:50:01,096
What a relief. That explains
everything. Thanks be to God.

678
00:50:01,163 --> 00:50:04,165
Look, Sister,
it was all a mistake.

679
00:50:08,671 --> 00:50:10,606
And if I talk to
Mr. McGuinn?

680
00:50:10,690 --> 00:50:12,924
Talk to him, by all means.

681
00:50:12,992 --> 00:50:14,359
But now that
the boy's secret's out,

682
00:50:14,477 --> 00:50:15,961
I'm gonna have to remove
him from the altar boys.

683
00:50:16,028 --> 00:50:17,528
That's what
I was trying to avoid.

684
00:50:17,596 --> 00:50:19,064
You were trying
to protect the boy.

685
00:50:19,131 --> 00:50:21,098
That's right.

686
00:50:21,166 --> 00:50:23,684
I might have done
the same thing.

687
00:50:23,752 --> 00:50:26,304
Is there a way Donald could
stay on the altar boys?

688
00:50:26,455 --> 00:50:30,525
If the boy drank altar wine, he
can't continue as an altar boy.

689
00:50:30,592 --> 00:50:31,993
Of course.

690
00:50:34,430 --> 00:50:36,414
Are you satisfied?

691
00:50:36,982 --> 00:50:37,983
Yes.

692
00:50:41,036 --> 00:50:43,038
Hmm.

693
00:50:43,106 --> 00:50:45,774
Well, I'll be going.
I have some writing to do.

694
00:50:47,042 --> 00:50:48,493
Intolerance.

695
00:50:48,561 --> 00:50:50,161
That's right.

696
00:50:51,864 --> 00:50:54,933
I'm not pleased
with how you handled this.

697
00:50:55,735 --> 00:50:57,568
Sister. Sister.

698
00:51:06,329 --> 00:51:07,629
Well...

699
00:51:09,732 --> 00:51:12,467
What a relief.
He cleared it all up.

700
00:51:15,420 --> 00:51:17,055
You believe him?

701
00:51:19,258 --> 00:51:20,759
Of course.

702
00:51:22,878 --> 00:51:25,981
Isn't it that it's easier
to believe him?

703
00:51:26,048 --> 00:51:28,350
But we can corroborate his
story with Mr. McGuinn.

704
00:51:28,417 --> 00:51:29,650
Mmm-hmm.

705
00:51:30,386 --> 00:51:31,552
Yes.

706
00:51:33,322 --> 00:51:35,741
These types of people
are clever.

707
00:51:39,578 --> 00:51:41,646
Well, I'm convinced.

708
00:51:41,648 --> 00:51:43,281
You're not.

709
00:51:43,348 --> 00:51:47,369
You just want things to be resolved
so you can have simplicity back.

710
00:51:48,721 --> 00:51:50,805
I want no further part of this.

711
00:51:52,324 --> 00:51:54,075
I'll bring him down.

712
00:51:55,795 --> 00:51:58,730
How can you be so sure
that he is lying?

713
00:52:02,584 --> 00:52:04,035
Experience.

714
00:52:06,656 --> 00:52:09,391
You just don't like him.

715
00:52:09,458 --> 00:52:12,844
You don't like it that
he uses a ballpoint pen.

716
00:52:12,912 --> 00:52:16,414
You don't like it that he takes
three lumps of sugar in his tea.

717
00:52:16,482 --> 00:52:18,683
You don't like it that he
likes <i>Frosty the Snowman,</i>

718
00:52:18,751 --> 00:52:23,555
and you are letting that convince you
of something terrible, just terrible.

719
00:52:25,007 --> 00:52:28,092
Well, I like
<i>Frosty the Snowman!</i>

720
00:52:28,161 --> 00:52:30,495
And I think it would be nice if this
school weren't run like a jail,

721
00:52:30,663 --> 00:52:32,897
and I think it's a good thing
that I love to teach history

722
00:52:32,965 --> 00:52:35,133
and that I might inspire
my students to love it, too.

723
00:52:35,201 --> 00:52:38,185
And if you judge that to mean that
I am not fit to be a teacher,

724
00:52:38,253 --> 00:52:39,921
then so be it!

725
00:52:43,476 --> 00:52:44,909
Sit down.

726
00:52:54,404 --> 00:52:57,672
Look at that.
You blew out my light.

727
00:53:01,294 --> 00:53:02,761
In ancient Sparta,

728
00:53:02,828 --> 00:53:06,514
important matters were decided
by who shouted loudest.

729
00:53:06,582 --> 00:53:09,734
Fortunately, we are not
in ancient Sparta.

730
00:53:15,991 --> 00:53:17,942
You honestly find
the students in this school

731
00:53:18,010 --> 00:53:21,763
to be treated like
inmates in a prison?

732
00:53:22,865 --> 00:53:24,799
No.

733
00:53:24,867 --> 00:53:29,954
Actually, they all seem fairly happy, but
they're all uniformly terrified of you.

734
00:53:31,691 --> 00:53:34,643
Yes.
That's how it works.

735
00:53:36,211 --> 00:53:37,679
Sit there.

736
00:53:53,512 --> 00:53:55,513
Hello, this is
Sister Aloysius Beauvier,

737
00:53:55,580 --> 00:53:59,167
principal at St. Nicholas School.
Is this Mrs. Miller?

738
00:54:01,320 --> 00:54:03,922
I'm calling about
your son, Donald.

739
00:54:17,970 --> 00:54:22,707
<i>A woman was gossiping with a
friend about a man she hardly knew.</i>

740
00:54:22,775 --> 00:54:24,409
<i>I know none of you
have ever done this.</i>

741
00:54:26,496 --> 00:54:29,197
<i>That night she had a dream.</i>

742
00:54:29,265 --> 00:54:35,136
<i>A great hand appeared over
her and pointed down at her.</i>

743
00:54:35,204 --> 00:54:40,342
<i>She was immediately seized with
an overwhelming sense of guilt.</i>

744
00:54:40,409 --> 00:54:43,011
<i>The next day she
went to confession.</i>

745
00:54:43,079 --> 00:54:46,114
<i>She got the old parish
priest, Father O'Rourke.</i>

746
00:54:47,216 --> 00:54:49,984
<i>She told him the whole thing.</i>

747
00:54:50,052 --> 00:54:54,822
<i>"Is gossiping a sin?"
she asked the old man.</i>

748
00:54:54,890 --> 00:54:58,994
<i>"Was that the hand of God
Almighty pointing a finger at me?</i>

749
00:54:59,061 --> 00:55:01,846
<i>"Should I be asking your
absolution, Father?</i>

750
00:55:01,913 --> 00:55:05,683
<i>"Tell me, have I done
something wrong?"</i>

751
00:55:05,751 --> 00:55:07,685
<i>"Yes."</i>

752
00:55:07,753 --> 00:55:09,337
<i>Father O'Rourke answered her.</i>

753
00:55:09,404 --> 00:55:14,391
<i>"Yes, you ignorant,
badly brought up female.</i>

754
00:55:14,459 --> 00:55:17,361
<i>"You have borne false witness
against your neighbor.</i>

755
00:55:17,429 --> 00:55:20,365
<i>"You have played fast and
loose with his reputation,</i>

756
00:55:20,432 --> 00:55:24,785
<i>"and you should be
heartily ashamed!"</i>

757
00:55:24,853 --> 00:55:30,541
<i>So the woman said she was sorry
and asked for forgiveness.</i>

758
00:55:30,609 --> 00:55:34,095
<i>"Not so fast," says O'Rourke.</i>

759
00:55:34,163 --> 00:55:38,767
<i>"I want you to go home.
Take a pillow up on your roof,</i>

760
00:55:38,834 --> 00:55:42,637
<i>"cut it open with a knife,
and return here to me."</i>

761
00:55:44,657 --> 00:55:48,576
<i>So the woman went home,
took a pillow off her bed,</i>

762
00:55:48,644 --> 00:55:50,244
<i>a knife from the drawer,</i>

763
00:55:50,312 --> 00:55:54,432
<i>went up the fire escape to her
roof and stabbed the pillow.</i>

764
00:55:54,500 --> 00:55:57,935
<i>Then she went back to the old
parish priest as instructed.</i>

765
00:55:58,003 --> 00:56:02,106
<i>"Did you gut the pillow
with a knife?" he says.</i>

766
00:56:02,174 --> 00:56:05,677
<i>"Yes, Father."
"And what was the result?"</i>

767
00:56:07,146 --> 00:56:09,714
<i>"Feathers," she said.</i>

768
00:56:13,652 --> 00:56:15,786
<i>"Feathers," he repeated.</i>

769
00:56:19,058 --> 00:56:21,459
<i>"Feathers everywhere, Father."</i>

770
00:56:24,230 --> 00:56:27,315
<i>"Now, I want you to go back</i>

771
00:56:27,382 --> 00:56:32,237
<i>"and gather up every last feather
that flew out on the wind."</i>

772
00:56:32,304 --> 00:56:37,325
<i>"Well," she said,
"it can't be done.</i>

773
00:56:37,392 --> 00:56:41,312
<i>"I don't know where they went.
The wind took them all over."</i>

774
00:56:43,148 --> 00:56:47,535
<i>"And that," said Father
O'Rourke, "is gossip!"</i>

775
00:56:50,055 --> 00:56:54,125
<i>In the name of the Father, the
Son and the Holy Ghost. Amen.</i>

776
00:56:58,564 --> 00:57:00,065
<i>Please rise.</i>

777
00:57:32,164 --> 00:57:34,816
What's that bird
complaining about?

778
00:57:37,102 --> 00:57:39,304
What kind of bird is that?

779
00:57:39,371 --> 00:57:42,257
That a starling?
A grackle?

780
00:57:45,194 --> 00:57:46,728
A crow.

781
00:57:47,212 --> 00:57:49,446
Course it is.

782
00:57:49,514 --> 00:57:51,749
Are you praying?
I didn't mean to interrupt.

783
00:57:51,751 --> 00:57:53,735
I'm not praying.
No.

784
00:57:55,570 --> 00:57:57,322
You seem subdued.

785
00:57:58,607 --> 00:58:01,392
Oh, I can't sleep.

786
00:58:02,577 --> 00:58:03,911
Why not?

787
00:58:05,748 --> 00:58:07,598
Bad dreams.

788
00:58:07,666 --> 00:58:11,102
Yeah, I can't sleep
on occasion.

789
00:58:11,170 --> 00:58:15,172
Why? Do you see that big hand
pointing a finger at you?

790
00:58:15,240 --> 00:58:16,824
Yes. Sometimes.

791
00:58:20,129 --> 00:58:23,698
Was your sermon directed
at anyone in particular?

792
00:58:24,700 --> 00:58:26,551
What do you think?

793
00:58:38,297 --> 00:58:42,766
I received a letter from
my brother in Maryland.

794
00:58:43,768 --> 00:58:45,303
He's very sick.

795
00:58:47,356 --> 00:58:49,641
Then maybe you should
go and see him.

796
00:58:49,708 --> 00:58:51,776
I can't leave my class.

797
00:59:00,653 --> 00:59:02,220
Is it true?

798
00:59:04,306 --> 00:59:05,523
What?

799
00:59:07,009 --> 00:59:09,277
You know what I'm asking.

800
00:59:11,347 --> 00:59:12,447
No.

801
00:59:15,618 --> 00:59:19,170
I saw you put an undershirt
in Donald Miller's locker.

802
00:59:21,640 --> 00:59:23,040
He left it in the sacristy.

803
00:59:23,108 --> 00:59:25,459
Why didn't you hand it to him?

804
00:59:29,165 --> 00:59:32,283
I'm trying to spare him
further embarrassment.

805
00:59:48,117 --> 00:59:51,268
It's me that cares about
that child, not her.

806
00:59:52,704 --> 00:59:55,206
Has she ever
reached out a hand?

807
00:59:57,092 --> 01:00:00,961
That black boy needs help
or he's not gonna make it.

808
01:00:01,030 --> 01:00:02,947
If she has her way, he'll
be left to his own undoing.

809
01:00:03,014 --> 01:00:06,467
Why do you think he drank the wine?
He's in trouble.

810
01:00:09,738 --> 01:00:12,006
And she sees me talk in a
human way to these kids

811
01:00:12,074 --> 01:00:17,145
and she immediately assumes that there
must be something wrong with it.

812
01:00:17,212 --> 01:00:20,398
Well, I'm not gonna let her keep
this parish in the Dark Ages,

813
01:00:20,466 --> 01:00:24,018
and I'm not gonna let her destroy
my spirit of compassion.

814
01:00:24,086 --> 01:00:25,653
I'm sure that's not her intent.

815
01:00:25,721 --> 01:00:27,722
That I care about
this congregation.

816
01:00:27,789 --> 01:00:29,657
I know you do.

817
01:00:29,659 --> 01:00:34,345
Like you care about your class.
You love them, don't you?

818
01:00:35,797 --> 01:00:38,616
Yes.
And that's natural.

819
01:00:38,684 --> 01:00:41,402
How else would
you relate to children?

820
01:00:44,289 --> 01:00:48,259
Now, I can look at your face
and know your philosophy.

821
01:00:48,326 --> 01:00:50,711
It's kindness.

822
01:00:50,779 --> 01:00:53,848
I don't know.
I mean, of course.

823
01:00:56,084 --> 01:01:00,338
There are people who go after
your humanity, Sister,

824
01:01:00,405 --> 01:01:02,707
that tell you that the light
in your heart is a weakness.

825
01:01:02,774 --> 01:01:05,760
Don't believe it.

826
01:01:05,827 --> 01:01:10,882
It's an old tactic of cruel people to
kill kindness in the name of virtue.

827
01:01:13,202 --> 01:01:15,687
There's nothing wrong
with love.

828
01:01:18,473 --> 01:01:19,657
Love?

829
01:01:21,493 --> 01:01:24,612
Have you forgotten the
message of our Savior?

830
01:01:24,679 --> 01:01:27,949
It's love of people.

831
01:01:37,342 --> 01:01:40,361
I just feel as if
everything is upside down.

832
01:01:45,550 --> 01:01:49,537
There are just times in life
when we feel lost. It happens.

833
01:01:52,474 --> 01:01:54,308
And it's a bond.

834
01:01:59,414 --> 01:02:00,814
Flowers.
Yeah.

835
01:02:01,767 --> 01:02:03,834
To remind me of spring.

836
01:02:13,245 --> 01:02:15,045
I should be going.

837
01:02:18,116 --> 01:02:20,551
I'm sorry your brother's ill.

838
01:02:22,237 --> 01:02:24,054
Thank you, Father.

839
01:02:30,145 --> 01:02:31,929
I don't believe it.

840
01:02:33,932 --> 01:02:35,449
You don't?

841
01:02:37,486 --> 01:02:38,669
No.

842
01:02:40,155 --> 01:02:42,940
Thank you, Sister.
Thank you very much.

843
01:02:54,502 --> 01:02:56,137
- Hey, Anthony!
- That's not funny.

844
01:02:56,204 --> 01:02:58,472
That's also the day
that I tripped. I broke my ankle.

845
01:02:58,540 --> 01:02:59,840
I barely...

846
01:02:59,908 --> 01:03:02,976
Father. I think I've just
gotta tell somebody.

847
01:03:03,045 --> 01:03:04,045
Hello, Noreen.

848
01:03:04,112 --> 01:03:06,414
I'm in love.

849
01:03:06,481 --> 01:03:08,682
That's wonderful.
Who's the lucky boy?

850
01:03:08,750 --> 01:03:09,850
Jimmy Hurley.

851
01:03:09,918 --> 01:03:11,485
Have you told him?

852
01:03:11,553 --> 01:03:13,470
For life and death,
I'd go for waffles.

853
01:03:13,538 --> 01:03:15,138
Maybe you should.

854
01:03:16,158 --> 01:03:17,691
Maybe I will, Father.

855
01:03:19,261 --> 01:03:20,411
Jimmy!

856
01:03:21,330 --> 01:03:23,047
Jimmy Hurley?

857
01:03:24,433 --> 01:03:25,983
Come over here!

858
01:03:28,887 --> 01:03:31,005
Hurry up, already!

859
01:03:31,073 --> 01:03:32,606
Father Sherman.

860
01:03:34,192 --> 01:03:36,426
Jimmy, I just
gotta tell you something.

861
01:03:42,617 --> 01:03:43,851
You dropped
something.

862
01:03:45,053 --> 01:03:46,253
It's not funny.

863
01:03:46,321 --> 01:03:47,521
Get out of the way.

864
01:04:01,703 --> 01:04:03,337
It's all right.

865
01:04:04,490 --> 01:04:05,589
He doesn't like me.

866
01:04:05,657 --> 01:04:07,108
That is so easy!

867
01:04:11,196 --> 01:04:13,514
My parents are
gonna be so angry at me.

868
01:04:21,457 --> 01:04:24,492
Okay. Be quiet.

869
01:04:27,345 --> 01:04:30,915
I said be quiet!

870
01:04:30,983 --> 01:04:34,652
The next one of you that speaks out of
turn gets sent right to the principal.

871
01:04:34,720 --> 01:04:37,238
Now the question was,

872
01:04:37,305 --> 01:04:40,341
what was Patrick
Henry's famous remark?

873
01:04:44,346 --> 01:04:45,496
Donald.

874
01:04:45,564 --> 01:04:46,731
Sister?

875
01:04:51,503 --> 01:04:53,270
What was the question?

876
01:04:54,740 --> 01:04:57,724
Nobody help him.
Jimmy, put your hand down.

877
01:04:58,593 --> 01:05:00,644
Donald Miller, stand up.

878
01:05:06,101 --> 01:05:08,452
What was the question, Donald?

879
01:05:08,520 --> 01:05:09,737
I don't know, Sister.

880
01:05:11,239 --> 01:05:14,007
It means you weren't listening.

881
01:05:14,075 --> 01:05:16,277
Yes, Sister.

882
01:05:16,294 --> 01:05:20,348
The question was, what was
Patrick Henry's famous remark?

883
01:05:24,269 --> 01:05:25,719
I don't know.

884
01:05:25,787 --> 01:05:27,171
"Give me liberty
or give me death!"

885
01:05:27,239 --> 01:05:30,041
James Hurley, down to
the principal's office.

886
01:05:30,108 --> 01:05:31,275
Now!

887
01:05:55,383 --> 01:05:56,500
Mrs. Miller?

888
01:05:56,567 --> 01:05:57,668
Yes.

889
01:05:57,736 --> 01:05:59,069
Come in.

890
01:06:00,972 --> 01:06:02,906
Please, have a seat.

891
01:06:06,895 --> 01:06:10,064
I was changing a bulb.

892
01:06:10,131 --> 01:06:13,034
Thought I mighta had the wrong day.
You didn't answer.

893
01:06:13,036 --> 01:06:14,101
Huh?

894
01:06:14,169 --> 01:06:17,504
Oh, well, just between us,

895
01:06:18,941 --> 01:06:22,743
I was listening to a transistor
radio with an earpiece.

896
01:06:22,810 --> 01:06:25,296
Look how tiny
they're making them.

897
01:06:25,363 --> 01:06:27,248
I confiscated it from
one of the students,

898
01:06:27,315 --> 01:06:29,082
now I can't stop
listening to it.

899
01:06:29,951 --> 01:06:31,585
You like music?

900
01:06:33,688 --> 01:06:36,356
No. News reports.

901
01:06:36,424 --> 01:06:38,976
Years ago I used to listen
to all the news reports,

902
01:06:39,010 --> 01:06:42,146
because my husband was
in Italy, in the war.

903
01:06:42,214 --> 01:06:44,331
You were a married woman?

904
01:06:44,399 --> 01:06:46,067
Yes.

905
01:06:46,134 --> 01:06:48,118
But then he was killed.

906
01:06:49,554 --> 01:06:50,921
Is your husband coming?

907
01:06:50,988 --> 01:06:53,624
Couldn't get off work.
I only have half an hour myself.

908
01:06:53,691 --> 01:06:56,760
I see. Of course.
It was a lot to ask.

909
01:07:06,171 --> 01:07:08,655
How's Donald doing?

910
01:07:08,723 --> 01:07:12,192
He's passing his subjects.
He has average grades.

911
01:07:12,260 --> 01:07:15,229
Oh. Good.

912
01:07:15,297 --> 01:07:18,048
He was upset about getting
taken off the altar boys.

913
01:07:18,115 --> 01:07:20,351
Mmm. Did he explain why?

914
01:07:20,385 --> 01:07:23,204
He said he was caught
drinking altar wine.

915
01:07:23,271 --> 01:07:25,556
That is the reason.

916
01:07:25,623 --> 01:07:28,325
Well, that seems fair.

917
01:07:29,961 --> 01:07:31,678
But he's a good boy, Sister.
He fell down there,

918
01:07:31,746 --> 01:07:34,497
but he's a good boy
pretty much down the line.

919
01:07:34,565 --> 01:07:36,550
How is he at home?

920
01:07:38,186 --> 01:07:40,454
His father beat the hell
out of him over that wine.

921
01:07:40,522 --> 01:07:42,055
Oh, he shouldn't do that.

922
01:07:42,123 --> 01:07:46,661
You don't tell my husband what to do.
You just stand back.

923
01:07:46,728 --> 01:07:50,264
My husband didn't want
Donald to come here.

924
01:07:50,332 --> 01:07:51,916
Why?
He thought he'd have trouble

925
01:07:51,983 --> 01:07:55,385
with the other boys, but
that hasn't really happened.

926
01:07:55,453 --> 01:07:57,088
Good.

927
01:07:57,090 --> 01:08:00,658
That priest, Father Flynn,
been watching out for him.

928
01:08:02,960 --> 01:08:04,160
Yes.

929
01:08:11,369 --> 01:08:13,086
Excuse me.

930
01:08:21,930 --> 01:08:23,998
James Hurley, what are
you doing out of class?

931
01:08:24,066 --> 01:08:25,106
Sister James sent me down.

932
01:08:25,166 --> 01:08:26,199
What for?

933
01:08:26,267 --> 01:08:27,467
Talking.

934
01:08:27,535 --> 01:08:29,186
Well, go back up and shut up!

935
01:08:30,422 --> 01:08:31,722
Go! Go!

936
01:08:36,027 --> 01:08:37,811
What's going on?

937
01:08:42,684 --> 01:08:46,103
None of your business.
Now go on. Go back to class.

938
01:08:46,888 --> 01:08:48,438
Bullshit.

939
01:08:48,506 --> 01:08:49,640
What'd you say?

940
01:08:49,708 --> 01:08:50,941
Nothing!

941
01:08:57,549 --> 01:08:58,849
You have 20 minutes, you say?

942
01:09:00,284 --> 01:09:03,070
It's just that I have
to walk to work.

943
01:09:03,137 --> 01:09:04,171
Where is work?

944
01:09:04,239 --> 01:09:05,873
Parkchester.

945
01:09:05,940 --> 01:09:09,093
If I don't start cleaning by noon,
I'm not home to let Donald in.

946
01:09:09,161 --> 01:09:11,011
May I walk with you?

947
01:09:11,546 --> 01:09:13,063
I don't mind.

948
01:09:15,433 --> 01:09:18,269
Eight sixty-fourths.

949
01:09:18,336 --> 01:09:21,555
Who can tell me what the
common denominator is?

950
01:09:21,623 --> 01:09:22,973
Nobody?

951
01:09:24,826 --> 01:09:27,695
Back already,
Mr. Hurley?

952
01:09:27,763 --> 01:09:29,563
I said, back already,
Mr. Hurley?

953
01:09:29,631 --> 01:09:31,615
Leave me alone!

954
01:09:31,683 --> 01:09:34,067
Who do you think
you're talking to?

955
01:09:34,135 --> 01:09:37,638
This is my classroom, boy!
Don't you forget that.

956
01:09:41,960 --> 01:09:43,477
I'm sorry.

957
01:09:49,867 --> 01:09:52,570
I'm sorry, Jimmy.

958
01:09:56,357 --> 01:09:58,592
Have you met
Father Flynn?

959
01:09:58,743 --> 01:09:59,843
Just seen him on the altar.

960
01:09:59,911 --> 01:10:01,144
Haven't met him face to face.

961
01:10:01,213 --> 01:10:03,681
No, just, you know,
heard from Donald.

962
01:10:03,748 --> 01:10:05,148
And what does he say?

963
01:10:05,217 --> 01:10:07,918
You know, "Father
Flynn, Father Flynn."

964
01:10:07,985 --> 01:10:10,754
He looks up to him. Man gives him his
time, which is what the boy needs.

965
01:10:10,822 --> 01:10:12,789
He needs that.

966
01:10:12,857 --> 01:10:16,727
Mrs. Miller, we may
have a problem.

967
01:10:16,794 --> 01:10:18,813
I thought there must a been a
reason you wanting to see me.

968
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:21,615
Principal's a big job.

969
01:10:21,683 --> 01:10:24,952
I just want to say though,
it's just till June.

970
01:10:25,019 --> 01:10:26,453
Excuse me?

971
01:10:28,222 --> 01:10:32,025
Whatever the problem is, Donald
just has to make it till June.

972
01:10:32,093 --> 01:10:34,411
Then he's off into high school.

973
01:10:34,478 --> 01:10:36,329
Right.

974
01:10:36,498 --> 01:10:38,315
If Donald can graduate
from St. Nicholas,

975
01:10:38,383 --> 01:10:41,184
he has a better chance of getting
into a good high school,

976
01:10:41,252 --> 01:10:45,322
and that would mean an
opportunity at college.

977
01:10:45,390 --> 01:10:47,157
I don't see anything
at this time

978
01:10:47,225 --> 01:10:50,760
standing in the way of his
graduating with his class.

979
01:10:51,796 --> 01:10:53,530
Well, that's all I care about.

980
01:10:53,597 --> 01:10:54,965
I doubt that.

981
01:10:55,533 --> 01:10:56,800
Try me.

982
01:10:59,554 --> 01:11:04,391
I am concerned about the relationship
between Father Flynn and your son.

983
01:11:04,459 --> 01:11:08,128
You don't say. Concerned.
What do you mean, concerned?

984
01:11:08,196 --> 01:11:10,297
That it may not be right.

985
01:11:11,867 --> 01:11:13,500
Well, there's something
wrong with everybody,

986
01:11:13,568 --> 01:11:17,371
and their soul gotta be forgiven.
I work right there.

987
01:11:17,438 --> 01:11:20,407
I am concerned, to be frank,

988
01:11:23,744 --> 01:11:27,714
that Father Flynn may have
made advances on your son.

989
01:11:31,820 --> 01:11:33,420
May have made?

990
01:11:34,222 --> 01:11:35,989
I can't be certain.

991
01:11:36,057 --> 01:11:37,123
No evidence?

992
01:11:37,191 --> 01:11:38,925
No.

993
01:11:38,993 --> 01:11:41,562
Then maybe
there's nothing to it.

994
01:11:49,003 --> 01:11:52,172
I think there is
something to it.

995
01:11:52,239 --> 01:11:54,942
I think Father Flynn gave
Donald that altar wine.

996
01:11:55,009 --> 01:11:57,177
Why would he do that?

997
01:12:00,247 --> 01:12:02,449
Has Donald been
acting strangely?

998
01:12:02,516 --> 01:12:03,584
No.

999
01:12:03,651 --> 01:12:04,772
Nothing out of the ordinary?

1000
01:12:04,819 --> 01:12:06,053
He's been himself.

1001
01:12:06,120 --> 01:12:07,287
All right.

1002
01:12:07,354 --> 01:12:08,889
Look, Sister, I don't
want any trouble.

1003
01:12:08,957 --> 01:12:11,257
I don't... I'm not sure
you completely understand.

1004
01:12:11,325 --> 01:12:13,293
I think I understand the kind
of thing you're talking about,

1005
01:12:13,360 --> 01:12:16,029
but I don't want
to get into it.

1006
01:12:16,130 --> 01:12:17,598
What's that?

1007
01:12:19,868 --> 01:12:22,603
Look, I only have a few minutes.
Not to be disagreeing,

1008
01:12:22,671 --> 01:12:25,539
but if we're talking about
something floating around

1009
01:12:25,607 --> 01:12:28,042
between this priest and my
son, it ain't my son's fault.

1010
01:12:28,109 --> 01:12:29,409
I'm not suggesting that...

1011
01:12:29,477 --> 01:12:30,711
He's just a boy.

1012
01:12:30,779 --> 01:12:32,279
I know.
Twelve years old.

1013
01:12:32,346 --> 01:12:33,747
If someone should be taking
blame, it should be the man...

1014
01:12:33,815 --> 01:12:34,882
I know. I agree
with you completely.

1015
01:12:34,950 --> 01:12:36,016
not the boy.

1016
01:12:36,084 --> 01:12:37,451
You're agreeing with me,
but I got called

1017
01:12:37,518 --> 01:12:38,619
to the principal, if you
know what I'm saying.

1018
01:12:38,687 --> 01:12:41,989
I am concerned about
Donald's welfare.

1019
01:12:44,125 --> 01:12:46,259
You honestly think that priest
gave Donald that wine to drink?

1020
01:12:46,327 --> 01:12:47,728
Yes, I do.

1021
01:12:47,796 --> 01:12:50,230
Then how come my son got
kicked off the altar boys

1022
01:12:50,298 --> 01:12:51,531
if it was a man
that gave it to him?

1023
01:12:51,600 --> 01:12:52,633
I know.

1024
01:12:52,701 --> 01:12:55,202
The boy got caught,
the man didn't.

1025
01:12:57,722 --> 01:12:59,156
So you're giving my son the blame.
No.

1026
01:12:59,223 --> 01:13:00,691
No problem my son
getting blamed,

1027
01:13:00,758 --> 01:13:02,258
and you know why that is.
Perhaps you should let me talk.

1028
01:13:02,326 --> 01:13:03,493
I think you're getting upset.

1029
01:13:03,561 --> 01:13:04,801
Sister, you ain't going against

1030
01:13:04,829 --> 01:13:05,896
no man in a robe and win.
He's got the position.

1031
01:13:05,963 --> 01:13:07,497
And he's got your son.

1032
01:13:07,565 --> 01:13:09,166
Let him have him then.

1033
01:13:11,452 --> 01:13:12,736
What?

1034
01:13:14,905 --> 01:13:16,806
It's just till June.

1035
01:13:18,893 --> 01:13:21,445
Do you know what you're saying?

1036
01:13:22,363 --> 01:13:24,581
Know more about it than you.

1037
01:13:26,467 --> 01:13:29,936
I believe this man is creating,

1038
01:13:30,004 --> 01:13:32,139
or may have already
brought about,

1039
01:13:32,206 --> 01:13:34,675
an improper relationship
with your son.

1040
01:13:34,742 --> 01:13:36,576
I don't know.

1041
01:13:36,644 --> 01:13:38,211
I know I am right.

1042
01:13:38,279 --> 01:13:42,349
Why you gotta know something like
that for sure when you don't?

1043
01:13:43,418 --> 01:13:45,719
What kind of mother are you?

1044
01:13:49,424 --> 01:13:52,459
Excuse me, but you don't know enough about
life to say a thing like that, Sister.

1045
01:13:52,527 --> 01:13:53,760
I know enough.

1046
01:13:53,828 --> 01:13:55,629
You know the rules maybe,
but that don't cover it.

1047
01:13:55,697 --> 01:13:57,597
I know what I won't accept.

1048
01:13:57,665 --> 01:13:59,800
You accept what you gotta
accept, and you work with it.

1049
01:13:59,867 --> 01:14:01,000
This man is in my school.

1050
01:14:01,068 --> 01:14:02,369
Well, he's gotta be
somewhere and

1051
01:14:02,437 --> 01:14:03,970
maybe he's doing some good, too.
He is after the boys!

1052
01:14:04,038 --> 01:14:07,140
Well, maybe some of them
boys want to get caught!

1053
01:14:19,437 --> 01:14:21,805
That's why his father beat him.

1054
01:14:25,443 --> 01:14:26,977
Not the wine.

1055
01:14:35,203 --> 01:14:37,270
What are you telling me?

1056
01:14:41,592 --> 01:14:44,428
I'm talking about
the boy's nature now,

1057
01:14:45,796 --> 01:14:47,897
not anything he's done.

1058
01:14:49,600 --> 01:14:53,736
You can't hold a child responsible
for what God gave him to be.

1059
01:14:56,307 --> 01:14:59,476
I'm only interested
in actions, Mrs. Miller.

1060
01:14:59,543 --> 01:15:01,461
But then there's
the boy's nature.

1061
01:15:01,529 --> 01:15:02,846
Leave that out of it.

1062
01:15:02,913 --> 01:15:04,614
Well, forget it then.

1063
01:15:06,016 --> 01:15:09,086
You're the one forcing
people to say things.

1064
01:15:12,640 --> 01:15:14,040
My boy came to your school

1065
01:15:14,108 --> 01:15:17,243
'cause they were gonna kill
him in the public school.

1066
01:15:20,147 --> 01:15:22,783
His father don't like him.

1067
01:15:22,850 --> 01:15:26,503
He come to your school,
kids don't like him.

1068
01:15:26,571 --> 01:15:30,140
One man is good to him,
this priest.

1069
01:15:30,208 --> 01:15:33,010
Then does a man
have his reasons, yes.

1070
01:15:34,145 --> 01:15:37,314
Everybody does.
You have your reasons,

1071
01:15:38,515 --> 01:15:41,651
but do I ask the man
why he's good to my son?

1072
01:15:43,570 --> 01:15:44,787
No.

1073
01:15:48,559 --> 01:15:50,327
I don't care why.

1074
01:15:53,798 --> 01:15:58,551
My son needs some man
to care about him

1075
01:15:59,821 --> 01:16:03,389
and to see him through
to where he wants to go.

1076
01:16:03,457 --> 01:16:05,658
And thank God this educated man

1077
01:16:05,726 --> 01:16:08,478
with some kindness in him
wants to do just that.

1078
01:16:08,546 --> 01:16:10,163
This will not do.

1079
01:16:10,231 --> 01:16:11,397
It's just till June.

1080
01:16:11,465 --> 01:16:13,400
I'll throw your son
out of this school.

1081
01:16:13,468 --> 01:16:15,668
And why would you do that
if it didn't start with him?

1082
01:16:16,004 --> 01:16:18,121
Because I will stop this.

1083
01:16:18,189 --> 01:16:20,140
You'd hurt my son
to get your way?

1084
01:16:20,207 --> 01:16:21,674
It won't end with your son.

1085
01:16:21,742 --> 01:16:22,992
Throw the priest out then.

1086
01:16:23,060 --> 01:16:25,462
I am trying to do just that.

1087
01:16:25,529 --> 01:16:27,731
Then what do you want from me?

1088
01:16:34,856 --> 01:16:36,189
Nothing.

1089
01:16:40,494 --> 01:16:43,196
As it turns out.

1090
01:16:43,264 --> 01:16:46,166
Please leave my son out of this.

1091
01:16:54,291 --> 01:16:57,994
My husband will kill that
child over a thing like this.

1092
01:17:07,455 --> 01:17:08,888
I will try.

1093
01:17:18,916 --> 01:17:20,283
I'm late.

1094
01:17:22,987 --> 01:17:24,287
Sister,

1095
01:17:27,124 --> 01:17:31,011
I don't know if you and me
on the same side.

1096
01:17:31,079 --> 01:17:35,682
I'll be standing with my son and
those who are good with my son.

1097
01:17:35,749 --> 01:17:39,286
It'd be nice to see you there.
Good morning.

1098
01:18:58,315 --> 01:19:00,483
May I come in?

1099
01:19:00,551 --> 01:19:02,285
A third party
would be required.

1100
01:19:02,353 --> 01:19:05,305
Yeah. What was Donald's
mother doing here?

1101
01:19:06,040 --> 01:19:07,274
We were having a chat.

1102
01:19:07,341 --> 01:19:08,608
About what?

1103
01:19:08,626 --> 01:19:10,126
A third party would truly
be required, Father.

1104
01:19:10,194 --> 01:19:11,994
No, Sister.
No third party!

1105
01:19:12,063 --> 01:19:14,797
Me and you are due for a talk!

1106
01:19:14,865 --> 01:19:17,350
You have to stop
this campaign against me.

1107
01:19:17,418 --> 01:19:19,152
You can stop it at any time.

1108
01:19:19,220 --> 01:19:20,387
How?

1109
01:19:20,471 --> 01:19:21,638
Confess and resign.

1110
01:19:21,706 --> 01:19:24,107
You are attempting
to destroy my reputation!

1111
01:19:24,175 --> 01:19:27,360
Who keeps opening my window?

1112
01:19:29,146 --> 01:19:30,797
What are you doing
in this school?

1113
01:19:30,865 --> 01:19:33,082
I'm trying to do good.

1114
01:19:33,150 --> 01:19:35,368
Even more to the point,

1115
01:19:35,436 --> 01:19:38,438
what are you doing
in the priesthood?

1116
01:19:38,506 --> 01:19:42,809
You are single-handedly holding
this school and this parish back.

1117
01:19:42,876 --> 01:19:43,910
From what?

1118
01:19:43,977 --> 01:19:45,044
Progressive education

1119
01:19:45,112 --> 01:19:46,313
and a welcoming church.

1120
01:19:46,380 --> 01:19:48,514
You can't distract me, Father.

1121
01:19:48,582 --> 01:19:50,116
This is not about my
behavior, it's about yours.

1122
01:19:50,184 --> 01:19:52,218
No, this is about
your unfounded suspicions.

1123
01:19:52,286 --> 01:19:54,137
That's right.
I have suspicions.

1124
01:19:54,205 --> 01:19:55,571
Just leave that.
It's not important.

1125
01:19:55,639 --> 01:19:57,607
I will decide

1126
01:20:00,561 --> 01:20:02,528
what's important.

1127
01:20:02,596 --> 01:20:05,448
Why do you suspect me?
What have I done?

1128
01:20:06,967 --> 01:20:10,653
You gave that boy wine, and
you let him take the blame.

1129
01:20:10,905 --> 01:20:13,940
That's completely untrue.
Did you talk to Mr. McGuinn?

1130
01:20:14,008 --> 01:20:16,326
All McGuinn knows
is that the boy drank wine.

1131
01:20:16,393 --> 01:20:18,828
He doesn't know
how he came to drink it.

1132
01:20:18,896 --> 01:20:20,831
Did his mother have
something to add to that?

1133
01:20:20,898 --> 01:20:22,065
No.

1134
01:20:23,050 --> 01:20:24,150
So that's it.

1135
01:20:24,218 --> 01:20:26,753
I am not satisfied.

1136
01:20:26,820 --> 01:20:29,088
Ask the boy then.

1137
01:20:29,156 --> 01:20:30,373
He'd protect you.

1138
01:20:30,441 --> 01:20:31,941
Why would he do that?

1139
01:20:31,976 --> 01:20:34,260
Because you have seduced him.

1140
01:20:34,328 --> 01:20:36,062
You're insane.

1141
01:20:36,130 --> 01:20:38,531
You've got it in your head
that I corrupted this child

1142
01:20:38,599 --> 01:20:41,701
after giving him wine, and
nothing I say will change that.

1143
01:20:41,769 --> 01:20:43,036
That's right.

1144
01:20:43,104 --> 01:20:44,938
But this has nothing
to do with the wine.

1145
01:20:45,005 --> 01:20:48,007
Not really. You've had a fundamental
mistrust of me before this incident.

1146
01:20:48,075 --> 01:20:51,962
It was you that warned Sister James
to be on the lookout, wasn't it?

1147
01:20:52,029 --> 01:20:53,280
That's true.

1148
01:20:53,347 --> 01:20:54,981
So you admit it!

1149
01:20:55,048 --> 01:20:56,382
Certainly.

1150
01:20:57,184 --> 01:20:58,485
Why?

1151
01:21:00,738 --> 01:21:02,305
I know people.

1152
01:21:03,741 --> 01:21:05,191
That's not good enough.

1153
01:21:05,259 --> 01:21:06,592
It won't have to be.

1154
01:21:06,660 --> 01:21:08,111
How's that?

1155
01:21:08,179 --> 01:21:10,897
You will tell me
what you have done.

1156
01:21:12,449 --> 01:21:14,334
Oh, I will.

1157
01:21:16,203 --> 01:21:17,637
Out again.

1158
01:21:19,240 --> 01:21:22,242
Sister James is convinced
I'm innocent.

1159
01:21:22,310 --> 01:21:25,478
So you talked to Sister James.

1160
01:21:25,546 --> 01:21:27,863
Well, of course
you talked to Sister James.

1161
01:21:27,931 --> 01:21:29,999
Did you know Donald's
father beats him?

1162
01:21:30,067 --> 01:21:31,384
Yes.

1163
01:21:31,452 --> 01:21:34,503
And might that not account
for the odd behavior

1164
01:21:34,605 --> 01:21:37,473
Sister James noticed
in the boy?

1165
01:21:37,542 --> 01:21:39,041
It might.

1166
01:21:39,109 --> 01:21:41,828
Then what is it? What?

1167
01:21:41,895 --> 01:21:44,130
What did you hear?

1168
01:21:44,198 --> 01:21:47,566
What did you see that
convinced you so thoroughly?

1169
01:21:49,136 --> 01:21:51,755
What does it matter?

1170
01:21:51,822 --> 01:21:56,209
It matters! What does it matter?
I want to know!

1171
01:22:08,021 --> 01:22:10,457
Out this window,

1172
01:22:10,524 --> 01:22:14,978
I saw you grab
William London's wrist,

1173
01:22:15,045 --> 01:22:18,915
and I saw him pull away.

1174
01:22:34,665 --> 01:22:35,932
Are you serious?

1175
01:22:36,000 --> 01:22:37,217
I am.

1176
01:22:38,468 --> 01:22:40,570
That's all?

1177
01:22:40,638 --> 01:22:43,472
Yeah. That was all.

1178
01:22:47,144 --> 01:22:49,011
That's nothing.

1179
01:22:50,898 --> 01:22:52,032
What are you doing now?

1180
01:22:52,099 --> 01:22:54,100
I'm writing down what you say.

1181
01:22:54,168 --> 01:22:58,804
It might be important when I have to
explain why you have to be removed.

1182
01:23:04,311 --> 01:23:07,897
This morning before I
spoke with Mrs. Miller,

1183
01:23:07,964 --> 01:23:11,317
I took the precaution of
calling your last parish.

1184
01:23:12,119 --> 01:23:13,803
What did he say?

1185
01:23:14,588 --> 01:23:16,356
Who?
The pastor.

1186
01:23:18,459 --> 01:23:22,929
I did not speak to the pastor.
I spoke to a nun.

1187
01:23:22,996 --> 01:23:25,898
You should have
spoken to the pastor.

1188
01:23:26,834 --> 01:23:28,485
I spoke to a nun.

1189
01:23:28,552 --> 01:23:30,720
You know that's not the proper route
for you to have taken, Sister.

1190
01:23:30,788 --> 01:23:33,923
The church is very clear.
You're supposed to go through the pastor.

1191
01:23:33,991 --> 01:23:36,726
Why? You have an
understanding, you and he?

1192
01:23:36,794 --> 01:23:39,829
No, you have no right to go
rummaging through my past!

1193
01:23:39,897 --> 01:23:41,765
You have a history.

1194
01:23:41,832 --> 01:23:44,567
This is your third parish
in five years.

1195
01:23:44,634 --> 01:23:46,135
Why?
Call the pastor.

1196
01:23:46,203 --> 01:23:48,905
Ask him why I left.
It's perfectly innocent.

1197
01:23:48,972 --> 01:23:50,456
I'm not calling the pastor.

1198
01:23:50,524 --> 01:23:51,975
I'm a good priest.

1199
01:23:52,042 --> 01:23:54,978
Go after another child and another
child, until you are stopped.

1200
01:23:55,045 --> 01:23:56,712
What nun did you speak to?

1201
01:23:56,797 --> 01:23:57,664
I won't say.

1202
01:23:57,732 --> 01:23:59,032
Yeah, I've not touched a child.

1203
01:23:59,100 --> 01:24:01,101
You have!

1204
01:24:01,168 --> 01:24:03,702
You haven't the slightest
proof of anything.

1205
01:24:03,804 --> 01:24:05,338
But I have my certainty.

1206
01:24:05,406 --> 01:24:07,590
And armed with that,
I'll go to your last parish

1207
01:24:07,658 --> 01:24:10,693
and the one before that.
If necessary, I'll find a parent.

1208
01:24:10,761 --> 01:24:14,163
Trust me, Father Flynn, I will.

1209
01:24:14,231 --> 01:24:17,967
You have no right
to act on your own!

1210
01:24:18,035 --> 01:24:22,255
You have taken vows,
obedience being one!

1211
01:24:22,323 --> 01:24:24,207
You answer to us!

1212
01:24:24,241 --> 01:24:27,326
You have no right to
step outside the church!

1213
01:24:27,394 --> 01:24:30,980
I will step outside the church
if that's what needs to be done,

1214
01:24:31,048 --> 01:24:32,848
though the door
should shut behind me!

1215
01:24:32,916 --> 01:24:37,987
I will do what needs to be done,
though I'm damned to hell!

1216
01:24:38,055 --> 01:24:42,459
You should understand that,
or you will mistake me.

1217
01:24:45,563 --> 01:24:48,731
Now, did you give Donald
Miller wine to drink?

1218
01:24:50,000 --> 01:24:52,568
Have you never done
anything wrong?

1219
01:24:53,453 --> 01:24:54,404
I have.

1220
01:24:54,471 --> 01:24:55,972
No mortal sin?

1221
01:25:05,048 --> 01:25:06,215
Yes.

1222
01:25:08,285 --> 01:25:09,369
And?

1223
01:25:12,089 --> 01:25:15,858
I confessed it, Father.

1224
01:25:18,529 --> 01:25:21,247
Then whatever I have done,

1225
01:25:21,314 --> 01:25:24,718
I have left in the healing
hands of my confessor.

1226
01:25:25,986 --> 01:25:27,470
As have you.

1227
01:25:29,006 --> 01:25:30,723
We are the same.

1228
01:25:35,078 --> 01:25:36,312
Mmm-mmm.

1229
01:25:38,732 --> 01:25:41,317
No, we are not.
We are not the same.

1230
01:25:51,829 --> 01:25:54,663
A dog that bites
is a dog that bites.

1231
01:25:56,917 --> 01:25:59,853
Did you give Donald
Miller wine to drink?

1232
01:26:01,021 --> 01:26:02,138
No.

1233
01:26:03,707 --> 01:26:05,808
Mental reservations?

1234
01:26:06,827 --> 01:26:07,977
No.

1235
01:26:11,098 --> 01:26:12,432
You lie.

1236
01:26:16,036 --> 01:26:17,670
Very well then.

1237
01:26:20,240 --> 01:26:24,394
If you will not
leave my office, I will.

1238
01:26:27,848 --> 01:26:30,783
And once I go, I will not stop.

1239
01:26:36,890 --> 01:26:38,124
Wait.

1240
01:27:04,818 --> 01:27:07,704
I can't say everything,
you understand?

1241
01:27:09,473 --> 01:27:11,741
There's things I can't say,

1242
01:27:13,727 --> 01:27:16,813
even if you can't imagine
the explanation, Sister.

1243
01:27:18,532 --> 01:27:23,052
Remember, there are things
beyond your knowledge.

1244
01:27:24,755 --> 01:27:29,775
Even if you feel certainty,
it is an emotion, not a fact.

1245
01:27:34,431 --> 01:27:36,633
You will request a transfer

1246
01:27:38,435 --> 01:27:41,788
and take a leave of absence
until it's granted.

1247
01:27:44,457 --> 01:27:47,193
You'd leave me nothing.

1248
01:27:47,260 --> 01:27:49,895
It's Donald Miller
who has nothing,

1249
01:27:51,248 --> 01:27:53,082
and you took
full advantage of that.

1250
01:27:53,150 --> 01:27:57,203
I've done nothing wrong.
I care about that boy.

1251
01:27:58,105 --> 01:27:59,305
Why?

1252
01:28:02,809 --> 01:28:04,911
'Cause you smile at him?

1253
01:28:05,963 --> 01:28:09,348
And you sympathize with him?

1254
01:28:09,416 --> 01:28:12,318
And you talk to him
as if you were the same?

1255
01:28:15,839 --> 01:28:18,307
You are a cheat.

1256
01:28:21,612 --> 01:28:25,164
And that warm feeling
you experienced

1257
01:28:25,232 --> 01:28:31,687
when that boy looked at you with trust
was not the sensation of virtue.

1258
01:28:31,755 --> 01:28:35,357
That could be got by any
drunkard with his tot of rum.

1259
01:28:37,427 --> 01:28:39,394
I can fight you.

1260
01:28:39,880 --> 01:28:41,497
You will lose.

1261
01:28:44,652 --> 01:28:46,769
Where's your compassion?

1262
01:28:49,173 --> 01:28:51,340
Nowhere you can get at it.

1263
01:28:54,728 --> 01:28:57,864
Stay here.
Compose yourself.

1264
01:28:59,549 --> 01:29:02,134
You can use the phone
if you'd like.

1265
01:29:03,553 --> 01:29:05,321
Good day, Father.

1266
01:29:16,650 --> 01:29:18,984
I have no sympathy for you.

1267
01:29:21,354 --> 01:29:24,606
I know you are invulnerable
to true regret.

1268
01:29:31,064 --> 01:29:32,915
And cut your nails.

